Consider the applications that transform vectors of $\mathbb{R}^3$ into vectors of $\mathbb{R}^2$.

$\begin{array}{cccc}
F:& \mathbb{R}^3 & \rightarrow  & \mathbb{R}^2 \\
  & (x, y, z) & \longrightarrow & (x-y^2, 2y+z)
\end{array}
\begin{array}{cccc}
G:& \mathbb{R}^3 & \rightarrow  & \mathbb{R}^2 \\
  & (x, y, z) & \longrightarrow & (x-y+z, 2y+z)
\end{array} 
